Reasoning: The paper deals with the problem of merging concurrent changes in a document, which is a common issue in collaborative software development and version control systems. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.SC (Symbolic Computation), cs.SE (Software Engineering), cs.PL (Programming Languages), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). However, since the paper focuses on the algorithmic aspect of the problem, cs.DS and cs.SC are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the practical implications of the algorithm, which could be relevant to cs.SE and cs.PL. Finally, the paper does not seem to involve any significant complexity analysis, which makes cs.CC less likely.
